India’s Foreign Reserves Fall $4.29 Billion to $316.5 Billion

-- B y   T u s h a r   D h a r a
-- 
2011-09-16T11:31:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/india-s-foreign-reserves-fall-4-29-billion-to-316-5-billion.html
India ’s foreign-exchange reserves
fell $4.29 billion to $316.5 billion in the week ended Sept. 9,
the Mumbai-based Reserve Bank of India said in an e-mailed
statement today.  Foreign-currency assets declined $4.17 billion to $280.7
billion, while the nation’s gold reserves were stable at $28.3
billion, the central bank said.  India’s special drawing rights with the International
Monetary Fund decreased $69 million to $4.55 billion while its
reserves with the IMF contracted $45 million to $2.93 billion.  Total reserves climbed by $32 billion in the past year, the
bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tushar Dhara in New Delhi at 
